.TH "iio_dma_buffer_set_length" 9 "iio_dma_buffer_set_length" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
iio_dma_buffer_set_length \- DMA buffer set_length callback
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" iio_dma_buffer_set_length
.BI "(struct iio_buffer *buffer "  ","
.BI "unsigned int length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "buffer" 12
Buffer to set the length for
.IP "length" 12
The new buffer length
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Should be used as the set_length callback for iio_buffer_access_ops
struct for DMA buffers.
